Class Logger

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      anar.Logger
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class Logger
extends java.lang.Thread

This class is used to log user's code and actions on sliders and keyboard during a run of the ANAR+ library. It is ONLY used in specific versions of the library which are being distributed for experimental purposes. Therefore no Logger instance will be initialized in a version downloaded from the httpANAR.ch website. If you still believe some data is being sent without your consent, please contact straight away admin@anar.ch. it makes use of ClientHttpRequest calss by Vlad Patryshev myjavatools.com
